        <div id="dsq-comment-body-58769" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-58769" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>From the dictionary<br />
Luxury: a state of great confort and elegance<br />
Premium: an amount to be paid &#8230;<br />
I don&#8217;t see Apple&#8217;s product as premium, that is an old song about the apple&#8217;s cost, a markup put on less valued products.<br />
It is not so. The 27&#8243; iMac cost less than competitor&#8217;s equivalent solution, the iPad air is unmatched in price by competitors, even without considering TCO, and on and on.<br />
Apple management of the supply chain can deliver quality products at competitive price mostly unmatched by competitors, more so if you consider TCO.<br />
